title: US federal agents shoot dead another person in Minneapolis
subhed: A video circulating on social media – and confirmed by authorities – shows several agents, including at least one wearing a vest marked 'POLICE,' surrounding a person on the ground and hitting him multiple times. Several gunshots are heard.

title: Brave1, the online armory supplying Ukraine's troops, reveals the limits of its efficiency
subhed: The platform, which was created to boost defense sector innovation and offset Russia's material superiority, helped Ukrainian units quickly obtain supplies. However, it also risks reaching a cap of technological sophistication.

title: Inside the workshop where dress forms are made
subhed: For 160 years, the French company Stockman has been handcrafting dress forms used by fashion designers, costume makers and aspiring stylists to refine their creations. This centuries-old expertise allows Stockman to meet custom requests from around the world.

title: France is considering banning phones in high schools. This school near Paris already does.
subhed: The Lycée Michelet, a large school complex with 2,300 students, banned mobile phones in its hallways in April 2025. School officials report positive results from a decision made in agreement with the entire educational community.

title: The RN's unspoken attraction to MAGA – and gradual ideological alignment
subhed: Like other European nationalists, Marine Le Pen has been put in a tough spot by Donald Trump's imperialist offensive. But the MAGA ideological campaign in Europe, of which France is a key target, has won over her Rassemblement National party over the past year.

title: 'As it ceases to inspire, the US is losing part of itself'
subhed: Donald Trump's second term has turned the United States into a threat to which the rest of the world has no choice but to adapt. Yet, over the past eight decades, habits and practices have taken root that will be used to counter this new imperialism, writes Le Monde columnist Gilles Paris.
